Line 9x5-inch loaf pan with aluminum foil, extending foil above sides of pan. Combine cookie crumbs and butter; press firmly on bottom and halfway up sides of prepared pan. In blender container, blend 1/4 cup peppermint candy and water until candy dissolves. In large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk, food coloring (optional), 1/2 cup crushed candy and peppermint liquid; mix well. Fold in whipped cream and remaining 1/4 cup crushed candy. Pour into prepared pan. Cover; freeze 6 hours or overnight. To serve, remove from pan; peel off foil and slice. Garnish as desired. Store leftovers covered in freezer.